DataElement.preferredName: Cervical Cancer American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC) Edition 7 Pathologic Tumor T Stage
DataElement.preferredDefinition: Extent of the primary cervical cancer based on evidence obtained from pathologic examination through completion of definitive surgery.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: Information related to pathologic T stage of a cervical tumor (or cancer of the uterine cervix).

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: Relating to a neck, or cervix, in any sense.:(NEE-o-PLAY-zha) Abnormal and uncontrolled cell growth.

Concepts.longName: Cervical
Concepts.definition: Relating to a neck, or cervix, in any sense.

Concepts.longName: Neoplasm
Concepts.definition: A benign or malignant tissue growth resulting from uncontrolled cell proliferation. Benign neoplastic cells resemble normal cells without exhibiting significant cytologic atypia, while malignant cells exhibit overt signs such as dysplastic features, atypical mitotic figures, necrosis, nuclear pleomorphism, and anaplasia. Representative examples of benign neoplasms include papillomas, cystadenomas, and lipomas; malignant neoplasms include carcinomas, sarcomas, lymphomas, and leukemias.

Property.preferredDefinition: Pathologic; caused by or altered by or manifesting disease or pathology.:One criteria of the TMN staging system.  T refers to the extent of tumor involvement at the primary site (T, followed by a number indicating size and depth of invasion).

Concepts.longName: Pathologic
Concepts.definition: Caused by or altered by or manifesting disease or pathology.

Concepts.longName: T Category
Concepts.definition: One criteria of the TNM staging system. T refers to the extent of tumor involvement at the primary site (T, followed by a number indicating size and depth of invasion).

ConceptualDomain.preferredDefinition: the process of identifying a disease by the signs and symptoms (NCI Glossary).

ValueDomain.preferredName: Cervical Cancer American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC) Edition 7 Pathologic T Stage
ValueDomain.preferredDefinition: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of cervical cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor._A group formed for the purpose of developing a system of clinical staging for cancer that is acceptable to the American medical profession and is compatible with other accepted classifications._The extent of a cancer within the body, especially whether the disease has spread from the original site to other parts of the body.

Concepts.longName: Cervical Cancer pT0 TNM Finding v7

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Cervical Cancer pT1 TNM Finding v7

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Cervical cancer confined to uterus (extension to corpus should be disregarded). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

Concepts.longName: Cervical Cancer pT1 TNM Finding v7

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Cervical Cancer pT1a TNM Finding v7

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Cervical Cancer pT1a TNM Finding v7
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Invasive cervical cancer diagnosed only by microscopy.  Stromal invasion with a maximum depth of 5.0 mm measured from the base of the epithelium and a horizontal spread of 7.0 mm or less.  Vascular space involvement, venous or lymphatic, does not affect classification. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

Concepts.longName: Cervical Cancer pT1a TNM Finding v7
Concepts.definition: Invasive cervical cancer diagnosed only by microscopy.  Stromal invasion with a maximum depth of 5.0 mm measured from the base of the epithelium and a horizontal spread of 7.0 mm or less.  Vascular space involvement, venous or lymphatic, does not affect classification. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Cervical Cancer pT1a1 TNM Finding v7

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Cervical Cancer pT1a1 TNM Finding v7
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Invasive cervical cancer with measured stromal invasion 3.0 mm or less in depth and 7.0 mm or less in horizontal spread. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

Concepts.longName: Cervical Cancer pT1a1 TNM Finding v7
Concepts.definition: Invasive cervical cancer with measured stromal invasion 3.0 mm or less in depth and 7.0 mm or less in horizontal spread. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Cervical Cancer pT1a2 TNM Finding v7

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Cervical Cancer pT1a2 TNM Finding v7
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Invasive cervical cancer with measured stromal invasion more than 3.0 mm and not more than 5.0 mm with a horizontal spread 7.0 mm or less. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

Concepts.longName: Cervical Cancer pT1a2 TNM Finding v7
Concepts.definition: Invasive cervical cancer with measured stromal invasion more than 3.0 mm and not more than 5.0 mm with a horizontal spread 7.0 mm or less. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
